{
  "doc_id": "7918",
  "text": "To construct strains carrying fusions of various regions upstream of ilvB, including bases Ϫ248 to 26, Ϫ187 to 26, and Ϫ667 to 26 ( Fig. 1 ) (base 1 is the transcription initiation base of the ilv-leu operon [CITATION_1] ), with lacZ in the amyE locus, the regions were amplified by using primers D-248F and Dϩ26R, primers D-187F and Dϩ26R, and primers D-667F and Dϩ26R (Table 2) , respectively, and DNA of strain 168 as the template. The PCR products were trimmed with XbaI and BamHI and then ligated with the XbaI-BamHI arm of plasmid pCREtest2 [CITATION_2] . The ligated DNAs were used for transformation of Escherichia coli strain DH5␣ to resistance to ampicillin (50 g/ml) on Luria-Bertani medium plates [CITATION_3] . The correct construction of the fusions in the resulting plasmids was confirmed by sequencing. The plasmids were linearized with PstI and then used for double-crossover transformation of strain 168 to resistance to chloramphenicol (5 g/ml) on tryptose blood agar base (Difco) plates containing 10 mM glucose (TBABG), which produced strains carrying the lacZ fusions FU676, FU709, and FU710, respectively. Strains carrying both the fusions and tnrA::Tn917, FU679 and FU712, were obtained by transformation of strains FU676 and FU710 with DNA of strain FU659 to erythromycin resistance, respectively.",
